---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="TED Talk Finder — Find the Best TED Talks on Any Topic"
  description="Discover the best TED talks on philosophy, life, communication, media, and more. AI-powered tool that verifies Simon Sinek, Amy Cuddy, Mel Robbins, Esther Perel, Bill Gates & Elon Musk TED talks directly from the official YouTube channel."
  canonicalUrl="https://tedtalksfinder.com/"
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <Header activePage="search" />

  <main class="flex-grow">
    <!-- Hero / Search Section -->
    <section
      class="bg-black text-white py-10 px-4 sm:py-16 sm:px-6 md:pt-24 md:pb-16 md:px-12 border-b border-gray-900"
    >
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center space-y-5 sm:space-y-8">
        <div class="space-y-3 sm:space-y-4">
          <p
            class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs md:text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#EB0028]"
          >
            Verified from Official TED YouTube Channel
          </p>
          <h1
            class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold tracking-normal uppercase leading-[1.05] flex flex-col items-center gap-3 sm:gap-4"
          >
            <span>Find the Best</span>
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3 sm:gap-5">
              <!-- Microphone icon — TED talk stage vibe -->
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="currentColor"
                class="text-[#EB0028] w-8 h-8 sm:w-14 sm:h-14 md:w-20 md:h-20 shrink-0 drop-shadow-[0_0_12px_rgba(235,0,40,0.5)]"
                aria-hidden="true"
              >
                <path d="M12 1a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v6a4 4 0 0 1-8 0V5a4 4 0 0 1 4-4z"
                ></path>
                <path
                  d="M19 11a1 1 0 1 0-2 0 5 5 0 0 1-10 0 1 1 0 1 0-2 0 7 7 0 0 0 6 6.92V21H9a1 1 0 1 0 0 2h6a1 1 0 1 0 0-2h-2v-3.08A7 7 0 0 0 19 11z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
              <span><span class="text-[#EB0028]">TED</span> Talks</span>
            </span>
          </h1>
        </div>
        <p
          class="text-gray-400 text-sm sm:text-base md:text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto font-normal leading-relaxed"
        >
          Search any topic — philosophy, communication, media, leadership and
          instantly get real, AI-curated TED talk videos verified directly from
          the official TED YouTube channel.
        </p>

        <!-- Search Form -->
        <form
          id="search-form"
          aria-label="Search for TED talks by topic"
          class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-5 sm:mt-8 flex flex-col gap-0 border border-gray-800 focus-within:border-[#EB0028] transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          <div class="relative flex-grow">
            <label for="search-input" class="sr-only"
              >Search TED talks by topic</label
            >
            <input
              type="text"
              id="search-input"
              name="q"
              placeholder="e.g. philosophy, communication, media..."
              autocomplete="off"
              class="w-full bg-[#1A1A1A] text-white px-4 py-3.5 sm:px-5 sm:py-4 border-0 focus:outline-none placeholder-gray-500 text-sm sm:text-base"
            />
          </div>
          <button
            type="submit"
            id="search-btn"
            aria-label="Find TED talks"
            class="bg-[#EB0028] text-white font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-sm px-8 py-3.5 sm:py-4 hover:bg-[#c40020] active:bg-[#a10019] transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center justify-center space-x-2 w-full cursor-pointer"
          >
            <span>Find Talks</span>
          </button>
        </form>

        <!-- Popular Topic Tags -->
        <nav aria-label="Popular TED talk topics">
          <div
            class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-1.5 sm:gap-2 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-[11px] sm:text-xs text-gray-400"
          >
            <span class="self-center font-semibold">Popular:</span>
            <button
              type="button"
              class="tag-btn border border-gray-800 px-3 py-1 hover:border-gray-500 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
              aria-label="Search TED talks about philosophy and life"
              >philosophy and life</button
            >
            <button
              type="button"
              class="tag-btn border border-gray-800 px-3 py-1 hover:border-gray-500 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
              aria-label="Search TED talks about communication"
              >communication</button
            >
            <button
              type="button"
              class="tag-btn border border-gray-800 px-3 py-1 hover:border-gray-500 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
              aria-label="Search TED talks about media">media</button
            >
            <button
              type="button"
              class="tag-btn border border-gray-800 px-3 py-1 hover:border-gray-500 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
              aria-label="Search TED talks about leadership">leadership</button
            >
            <button
              type="button"
              class="tag-btn border border-gray-800 px-3 py-1 hover:border-gray-500 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
              aria-label="Search TED talks about procrastination"
              >procrastination</button
            >
            <button
              type="button"
              class="tag-btn border border-gray-800 px-3 py-1 hover:border-gray-500 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
              aria-label="Search TED talks about mental health"
              >mental health</button
            >
            <button
              type="button"
              class="tag-btn border border-gray-800 px-3 py-1 hover:border-gray-500 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
              aria-label="Search TED talks about AI ethics">AI ethics</button
            >
          </div>
        </nav>

        <!-- Hero Page Links -->
        <div
          class="flex flex-wrap justify-center items-center gap-x-3 sm:gap-x-4 gap-y-1.5 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-[10px] sm:text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-500 font-semibold pt-1"
        >
          <a
            href="/about"
            class="hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150">About Us</a
          >
          <span class="text-gray-800 select-none">•</span>
          <a
            href="/privacy-policy"
            class="hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
            >Privacy Policy</a
          >
          <span class="text-gray-800 select-none">•</span>
          <a
            href="/terms-and-conditions"
            class="hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
            >Terms & Conditions</a
          >
          <span class="text-gray-800 select-none">•</span>
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150"
            >Contact Us</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Results Section -->
    <section
      id="results-section"
      class="py-10 px-4 sm:py-16 sm:px-6 md:py-20 md:px-12 bg-[#F4F4F4] min-h-[400px] flex items-center justify-center"
    >
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto w-full">
        <!-- Initial Blank State -->
        <div
          id="initial-state"
          class="text-center py-8 sm:py-12 max-w-md mx-auto space-y-3 sm:space-y-4"
        >
          <div class="text-gray-400 text-5xl sm:text-6xl font-light">💡</div>
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wide">
            Enter a topic
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-500 px-2">
            Discover top-rated TED talks on procrastination, space, psychology,
            design, or any subject you want to dive into.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Homepage Recent Uploads Feed Section -->
        <div
          id="homepage-recent"
          class="mt-8 sm:mt-12 pt-8 sm:pt-12 border-t border-gray-300 space-y-6 sm:space-y-8 w-full"
        >
          <div
            class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-start sm:items-center border-b border-gray-300 pb-3 sm:pb-4 gap-1.5 sm:gap-2"
          >
            <h2
              class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black"
            >
              Featured Recent Talks
            </h2>
            <span
              class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold text-gray-500 bg-gray-200 px-2.5 py-1 rounded"
              >LATEST ON TED</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            id="homepage-recent-grid"
            class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5 sm:gap-8"
          >
            <div
              class="text-center py-10 text-gray-400 col-span-full animate-pulse text-sm"
            >
              Loading featured recent talks...
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Loading State -->
        <div id="loading-state" class="hidden w-full">
          <!-- Hero -->
          <div
            class="relative py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col items-center text-center gap-8 overflow-hidden"
          >
            <!-- Mic with ripples -->
            <div class="relative flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="ted-ring"></span>
              <span
                class="ted-ring"
                style="animation-delay: 0.8s; border-color: rgba(235,0,40,0.25);"
              ></span>
              <span
                class="ted-ring"
                style="animation-delay: 1.6s; border-color: rgba(235,0,40,0.12);"
              ></span>
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="currentColor"
                class="relative z-10 w-12 h-12 sm:w-14 sm:h-14 text-[#EB0028] ted-mic"
                aria-hidden="true"
              >
                <path d="M12 1a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v6a4 4 0 0 1-8 0V5a4 4 0 0 1 4-4z"
                ></path>
                <path
                  d="M19 11a1 1 0 1 0-2 0 5 5 0 0 1-10 0 1 1 0 1 0-2 0 7 7 0 0 0 6 6.92V21H9a1 1 0 1 0 0 2h6a1 1 0 1 0 0-2h-2v-3.08A7 7 0 0 0 19 11z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>

            <!-- Single line of text -->
            <p
              class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold text-gray-500 tracking-wide"
            >
              Searching for the best talks on
              <span class="text-[#EB0028] font-extrabold"
                >&ldquo;<span id="loading-keyword">&hellip;</span>&rdquo;</span
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Skeleton cards -->
          <div
            class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5 sm:gap-8"
          >
            {
              [1, 2, 3].map(() => (
                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 flex flex-col h-full animate-pulse">
                  <div class="aspect-video bg-gray-200 w-full" />
                  <div class="p-6 flex flex-col flex-grow space-y-4">
                    <div class="h-3 bg-gray-200 w-1/3 rounded" />
                    <div class="h-5 bg-gray-200 w-5/6 rounded" />
                    <div class="h-3 bg-gray-200 w-full rounded" />
                    <div class="h-3 bg-gray-200 w-2/3 rounded" />
                    <div class="mt-auto pt-4 h-9 bg-gray-100 w-full" />
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))
            }
          </div>
        </div>

        <style>
          .ted-ring {
            position: absolute;
            width: 72px;
            height: 72px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            border: 1.5px solid rgba(235, 0, 40, 0.45);
            animation: tedRipple 2.4s ease-out infinite;
          }
          @keyframes tedRipple {
            0% {
              transform: scale(0.9);
              opacity: 1;
            }
            100% {
              transform: scale(2.8);
              opacity: 0;
            }
          }
          .ted-mic {
            animation: tedMic 1.8s ease-in-out infinite;
          }
          @keyframes tedMic {
            0%,
            100% {
              filter: drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(235, 0, 40, 0.5));
            }
            50% {
              filter: drop-shadow(0 0 20px rgba(235, 0, 40, 0.9));
              transform: scale(1.06);
            }
          }
        </style>

        <!-- Error State -->
        <div
          id="error-state"
          class="hidden text-center py-12 max-w-md mx-auto space-y-4"
        >
          <div class="text-[#EB0028] text-6xl">⚠️</div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wide">
            Search Failed
          </h2>
          <p id="error-text" class="text-gray-600">
            Couldn't find verified talks — try a different topic.
          </p>
          <button
            id="retry-btn"
            class="border border-black px-6 py-2 uppercase font-bold text-xs hover:bg-black hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150 cursor-pointer"
            >Try Again</button
          >
        </div>

        <!-- Success Results State -->
        <div id="success-state" class="hidden space-y-10 sm:space-y-16 w-full">
          <!-- Curated Talks Section -->
          <div class="space-y-5 sm:space-y-8">
            <div
              class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-start sm:items-center border-b border-gray-300 pb-3 sm:pb-4 gap-1.5 sm:gap-2"
            >
              <h2
                id="results-title"
                class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight"
              >
              </h2>
              <span
                class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold text-[#EB0028] bg-red-50 border border-red-100 px-2.5 py-1 rounded"
                >CURATED OFFICIAL TALKS</span
              >
            </div>

            <div
              id="results-grid"
              class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5 sm:gap-8"
            >
              <!-- Dynamically populated curated cards go here -->
            </div>

            <!-- Show More Pagination Button -->
            <div class="flex justify-center pt-2 sm:pt-4">
              <button
                id="show-more-btn"
                class="hidden border-2 border-black text-black px-8 sm:px-10 py-3 sm:py-4 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-xs hover:bg-black hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150 cursor-pointer w-full sm:w-auto"
              >
                Show More Talks
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Recent Talks Section (Within 1 Year) -->
          <div id="recent-section" class="space-y-5 sm:space-y-8 hidden">
            <div
              class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-start sm:items-center border-b border-gray-300 pb-3 sm:pb-4 gap-1.5 sm:gap-2"
            >
              <h2
                class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight"
              >
                Latest Uploads <span class="text-[#EB0028]"
                  >(Within 1 Year)</span
                >
              </h2>
              <span
                class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold text-gray-500 bg-gray-200 px-2.5 py-1 rounded"
                >RECENT UPLOADS</span
              >
            </div>

            <div
              id="recent-grid"
              class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5 sm:gap-8"
            >
              <!-- Dynamically populated recent cards go here -->
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- SEO Content Article Section -->
  <section
    aria-label="About TED Talk Finder"
    class="bg-white border-t border-gray-200 py-12 px-4 sm:py-16 sm:px-6 md:py-20 md:px-12"
  >
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Section Header -->
      <div class="mb-8 sm:mb-12 border-b border-gray-200 pb-6 sm:pb-8">
        <p
          class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#EB0028] mb-2 sm:mb-3"
        >
          About This Tool
        </p>
        <h2
          class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black leading-tight"
        >
          What Is TED Talk Finder & How Does It Work?
        </h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Article Content -->
      <article
        class="prose-content space-y-4 sm:space-y-6 text-gray-700 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed"
      >
        <p>
          <strong>TED Talk Finder</strong> is a free, AI-powered search tool that
          helps you discover the <strong>best TED talks</strong> on virtually any
          subject — from philosophy and life to communication, media, leadership,
          science, technology, and beyond. Whether you're a student, professional,
          researcher, or lifelong learner, this tool makes it effortless to explore
          the vast library of <strong>TED talk videos</strong> available on YouTube.
        </p>

        <h3
          class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-2 sm:mb-3"
        >
          What Is a TED Talk?
        </h3>
        <p>
          The <strong>TED talk meaning</strong> traces back to 1984, when TED — short
          for <em>Technology, Entertainment, and Design</em> — held its first conference.
          Today, TED is a global non-profit dedicated to spreading ideas through short,
          powerful talks. A <strong>TED talk</strong> is typically an 18-minute (or
          shorter) presentation delivered by world-leading thinkers, innovators, and
          researchers. Available free at <strong>TED talk YouTube</strong> and on
          ted.com, these talks have collectively been viewed billions of times across
          the globe.
        </p>

        <h3
          class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-2 sm:mb-3"
        >
          Best TED Talks on Philosophy &amp; Life
        </h3>
        <p>
          If you're searching for the <strong
            >best TED talks about philosophy and life</strong
          >, this tool delivers verified results in seconds. Talks in this
          category explore happiness, meaning, identity, resilience, and the
          human condition. Legendary TED speakers like Brené Brown on
          vulnerability, Dan Gilbert on happiness, and Viktor Frankl-inspired
          talks on finding meaning make this one of the richest topic categories
          available. TED Talk Finder uses AI to surface the most relevant and
          highest-impact talks so you never have to wade through irrelevant
          results.
        </p>

        <h3
          class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-2 sm:mb-3"
        >
          Best TED Talks About Communication
        </h3>
        <p>
          The <strong>best TED talks about communication</strong> cover everything
          from public speaking confidence to active listening, storytelling, and persuasion.
          Notable talks include Julian Treasure's "How to speak so that people want
          to listen" and Celeste Headlee's "10 ways to have a better conversation."
          TED Talk Finder lets you search for these directly and also surfaces recent
          uploads from the official TED channel, so you always have access to fresh
          content.
        </p>

        <h3
          class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-2 sm:mb-3"
        >
          TED Talks on Media — Understanding the Information Age
        </h3>
        <p>
          Looking for a <strong>TED talk on media</strong> or a <strong
            >media TED talk</strong
          >? TED has produced dozens of powerful talks exploring journalism,
          social media, fake news, digital culture, and the future of
          storytelling. Whether you want to understand the <strong
            >TED talk about media</strong
          >'s role in shaping public opinion or explore how algorithms influence
          what we read and watch, TED Talk Finder surfaces verified talks from
          credible voices at the intersection of technology and media.
        </p>

        <h3
          class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-2 sm:mb-3"
        >
          Famous TED Talks You Should Watch
        </h3>
        <p>
          Some of the most widely shared <strong>TED talk topics</strong> include:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-2 pl-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#EB0028] font-bold mt-0.5">→</span><span
              ><strong>Simon Sinek TED talk</strong> — "How Great Leaders Inspire
              Action" is one of the most-watched TED talks in history, introducing
              the "Golden Circle" framework for purpose-driven leadership.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#EB0028] font-bold mt-0.5">→</span><span
              ><strong>Amy Cuddy TED talk</strong> — "Your Body Language May Shape
              Who You Are" explores how power poses influence confidence and hormonal
              responses, with practical implications for job interviews and public
              speaking.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#EB0028] font-bold mt-0.5">→</span><span
              ><strong>Mel Robbins TED talk</strong> — "How to Stop Screwing Yourself
              Over" delivers a punchy, no-nonsense breakdown of self-motivation and
              the 5-second rule for beating hesitation.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#EB0028] font-bold mt-0.5">→</span><span
              ><strong>Esther Perel TED talk</strong> — Known for talks on desire,
              love, and infidelity, Esther Perel's TED presentations are among the
              most honest and nuanced explorations of modern relationships.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#EB0028] font-bold mt-0.5">→</span><span
              ><strong>Bill Gates TED talks</strong> — Bill Gates has delivered multiple
              TED talks covering global health, climate change, pandemic preparedness,
              and education reform.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#EB0028] font-bold mt-0.5">→</span><span
              ><strong>Elon Musk TED talks</strong> — Elon Musk's TED appearances
              dive deep into SpaceX, Tesla, the future of transportation, and the
              existential importance of becoming a multi-planetary species.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3
          class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-2 sm:mb-3"
        >
          How AI Powers TED Talk Finder
        </h3>
        <p>
          At its core, TED Talk Finder uses a <strong
            >large language model (LLM)</strong
          > — Google Gemini or Grok — to generate a curated list of relevant TED talk
          titles and speakers for your search query. Each suggestion is then verified
          in real-time against the <strong>official TED YouTube channel</strong
          >, ensuring you only see talks that truly exist and are publicly
          available. Duration filtering ensures no YouTube Shorts or promo clips
          appear — only full, long-form TED talk presentations. Results are
          cached intelligently, so repeat searches are instant.
        </p>

        <h3
          class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-2 sm:mb-3"
        >
          Exploring TED Talk Topics
        </h3>
        <p>
          Beyond the famous speakers, TED Talk Finder excels at surfacing talks
          on niche <strong>TED talk topics</strong> you might not find easily by browsing
          YouTube. Search for "creativity," "climate change," "neuroscience," "sleep,"
          "mindfulness," or "artificial intelligence" — and the tool will return a
          carefully curated, verified shortlist of the most relevant TED talks available.
          A dedicated "Recent Uploads" section also surfaces TED talks published within
          the last year, keeping you informed with the freshest ideas worth spreading.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 border-t border-gray-200 pt-6 mt-8">
          <em
            >TED Talk Finder is an independent fan-built tool and is not
            affiliated with or endorsed by TED Conferences LLC. All TED talk
            videos are sourced from the official TED YouTube channel and remain
            the intellectual property of their respective speakers and TED.</em
          >
        </p>
      </article>

      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <div class="mt-10 sm:mt-16">
        <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8 border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 sm:pb-6">
          <p
            class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#EB0028] mb-2 sm:mb-3"
          >
            Common Questions
          </p>
          <h2
            class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black"
          >
            Frequently Asked Questions
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div
          class="space-y-0 divide-y divide-gray-200"
          itemscope
          itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage"
        >
          <details
            class="group py-6"
            itemscope
            itemprop="mainEntity"
            itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
          >
            <summary
              class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none"
            >
              <h3
                class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-black group-open:text-[#EB0028] transition-colors"
                itemprop="name"
              >
                What is a TED talk?
              </h3>
              <span
                class="text-[#EB0028] text-xl font-light ml-4 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform"
                >+</span
              >
            </summary>
            <div
              class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
              itemscope
              itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
              itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"
            >
              <p itemprop="text">
                A TED talk is a short, influential presentation given at a TED
                (Technology, Entertainment, Design) conference or partner event
                (like TEDx). Typically lasting 18 minutes or less, TED talks
                cover diverse subjects including science, technology, business,
                culture, design, and personal growth. They are recorded and
                distributed free of charge online to spread "ideas worth
                spreading."
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details
            class="group py-6"
            itemscope
            itemprop="mainEntity"
            itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
          >
            <summary
              class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none"
            >
              <h3
                class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-black group-open:text-[#EB0028] transition-colors"
                itemprop="name"
              >
                What does TED talk stand for?
              </h3>
              <span
                class="text-[#EB0028] text-xl font-light ml-4 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform"
                >+</span
              >
            </summary>
            <div
              class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
              itemscope
              itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
              itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"
            >
              <p itemprop="text">
                TED stands for Technology, Entertainment, and Design. These
                three broad subject areas originally shaped the first TED
                conference in 1984. Today, TED talks have expanded far beyond
                these topics to include sciences, humanities, business, design,
                global issues, and personal growth.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details
            class="group py-6"
            itemscope
            itemprop="mainEntity"
            itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
          >
            <summary
              class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none"
            >
              <h3
                class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-black group-open:text-[#EB0028] transition-colors"
                itemprop="name"
              >
                What are the top 10 TED Talks of all time?
              </h3>
              <span
                class="text-[#EB0028] text-xl font-light ml-4 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform"
                >+</span
              >
            </summary>
            <div
              class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
              itemscope
              itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
              itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"
            >
              <p itemprop="text">
                The top 10 most-viewed and popular TED talks of all time
                include: 1. "Do schools kill creativity?" by Sir Ken Robinson,
                2. "Your body language may shape who you are" by Amy Cuddy, 3.
                "How great leaders inspire action" by Simon Sinek, 4. "The power
                of vulnerability" by Brené Brown, 5. "Inside the mind of a
                master procrastinator" by Tim Urban, 6. "10 ways to have a
                better conversation" by Celeste Headlee, 7. "The next outbreak?
                We're not ready" by Bill Gates, 8. "My stroke of insight" by
                Jill Bolte Taylor, 9. "What makes a good life? Lessons from the
                longest study on happiness" by Robert Waldinger, and 10. "The
                puzzle of motivation" by Dan Pink.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details
            class="group py-6"
            itemscope
            itemprop="mainEntity"
            itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
          >
            <summary
              class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none"
            >
              <h3
                class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-black group-open:text-[#EB0028] transition-colors"
                itemprop="name"
              >
                Why is TED Talk so famous?
              </h3>
              <span
                class="text-[#EB0028] text-xl font-light ml-4 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform"
                >+</span
              >
            </summary>
            <div
              class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
              itemscope
              itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
              itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"
            >
              <p itemprop="text">
                TED talks are famous because they synthesize complex ideas into
                short, engaging, and highly visual presentations that are easily
                digestible. The format's strict 18-minute limit forces speakers
                to be concise and impactful. Combined with free online
                distribution, high production quality, and speakers who are
                world-class experts or have unique stories, TED talks quickly
                spread across social media.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details
            class="group py-6"
            itemscope
            itemprop="mainEntity"
            itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
          >
            <summary
              class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none"
            >
              <h3
                class="text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-black group-open:text-[#EB0028] transition-colors"
                itemprop="name"
              >
                What is the most successful Ted talk in history?
              </h3>
              <span
                class="text-[#EB0028] text-xl font-light ml-4 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform"
                >+</span
              >
            </summary>
            <div
              class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
              itemscope
              itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
              itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"
            >
              <p itemprop="text">
                Sir Ken Robinson's 2006 presentation, "Do schools kill
                creativity?", is widely considered the most successful and
                popular TED talk in history. It has garnered over 75 million
                views on the official TED website and YouTube channel, sparking
                a global conversation about educational systems and creativity.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

