              >
                how to do a ted talk
              </h3>
              <span
                class="text-[#EB0028] text-xl font-light ml-4 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform"
                >+</span
              >
            </summary>
            <div
              class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
              itemscope
              itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
              itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"
            >
              <p itemprop="text">
                To give a TED talk, you should: 1. Define your core "idea worth
                spreading" clearly, 2. Apply or get nominated to speak at a main
                TED event or apply directly to a local, independent TEDx event,
                3. Outline your talk focusing on a narrative structure, 4. Keep
                it under 18 minutes, and 5. Rehearse extensively to deliver a
                memorable, conversational presentation without notes.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

